Limpopo premier Stanley Mathabatha has launched the province's community-based hotspots eradication strategy to curb the spread of COVID-19. POLOKWANE - Limpopo premier Stanley Mathabatha has launched the province's community-based hotspots eradication strategy to curb the spread of COVID-19. There has been a rapid rise in infections after 19 confirmed cases were uncovered at Marula mine. Mathabatha said the main problems facing the community are rooted in accessibility. WATCH: Limpopo welcomes Cuban healthcare workers He said, "the issue is health services and roads. Even where there are clinics, the problem is accessibility because of roads." The premier stated he would be taking strong decisions to provide health to the community. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.